  "response": "A mature alpha male chimpanzee would likely be stronger than a human, even an extremely strong human like Haf\u00fe\u00f3r J\u00fal\u00edus Bj\u00f6rnsson (The Mountain). Chimpanzees have incredible strength due to their muscular structure and evolutionary adaptations. Studies suggest that a chimpanzee can be 4-7 times stronger than a similarly sized human, with some estimates indicating they could lift up to 10 times more weight. \n\nWhile Bj\u00f6rnsson is incredibly strong by human standards (he won World's Strongest Man competitions), a mature male chimpanzee would likely overpower him due to their natural muscle density, skeletal structure, and lack of neural inhibitors that limit human muscle exertion. A chimp's muscle fibers are configured differently, allowing for greater raw physical power relative to body size.\n\nSo in a direct strength comparison, the chimpanzee would almost certainly be the stronger competitor, despite the human's impressive athletic achievements.",
